annouce our desire to develop the Nb8 actively with Nc6. The downside is White
gets the active possibility of Ne5 (next chapter) but 8. h5 is also natural.
We can respond with an immediate 11...c5 which is very tempting since White's
most popular responses score very poorly. However White could get a slightly
better endgame with percise play, although nothing fatal. 11...Be7 is another
option with a later c5. We should also not be worried about losing the c5 pawn
as in many variations we get strong compensation with the d5 outpost and
multiple pawn weaknesses in White's camp.} *

