Chennai 2013  Summary: The "old" line with Bb4+ is still viable in leading to
complex opposite side castling positions. In usual Caro fasion Black will rely
on light square play with ideas such as h5!? (to stop g4) or Qd5! (to trade
queens). Obviously the most secure way of obtaining counterchances is with a
timely c6-c5. I think these are good fighting lines but also need to handled
with care as White has strong kingside potential due to our h6 pawn hook} *

