{Let's tie up the loose ends by checking out side options for White} 1. e4 c6
2. d3 {It may seem strange to only push the d-pawn one square but there are
some players who love to setup a Kings Indian structure no matter what. Of
course here we can take over the center} (2. Nc3 d5 {Aside from transposing to
main lines White can try two tricky queen moves} 3. Qf3 $5 (3. Qe2 {Has a
peculiar idea} d4 4. Nd1 {White wants to play f4 later and then Nd1-Nf2 to
attack on the kingside} e5 5. g3 c5 {Grabbing the available space} 6. d3 Nc6 7.
Bg2 Bd6 8. f4 (8. Nh3 f6 9. f4 Be6 10. O-O Qd7 11. fxe5 Nxe5 $15 {0-1 (45)
Voitsekhovsky,S (2523)-Tomashevsky,E (2709) Ekaterinburg 2013}) 8... exf4 9.
gxf4 f6 (9... Qc7 10. e5 Be7 11. Nf3 Nh6 12. Nf2 Nf5 13. Ne4 Be6 14. a3 h6 $13
{0-1 (78) Petenyi,T (2459)-Wojtaszek,R (2736) Bilbao 2014}) 10. Nf3 Nge7 11.
O-O Qc7 12. Nh4 Be6 13. e5 fxe5 14. f5 Bf7 15. Nf2 O-O-O $17 {0-1 (71)
Pridorozhni,A (2565)-Moskalenko,A (2531) Sochi 2017}) 3... dxe4 {A simple
solution} (3... d4 $5 {This falls into a "trap" but keeps the game more complex
} 4. Bc4 e6 5. Nce2 c5 6. d3 Nc6 7. Qg3 h5 8. h4 b5 9. Bb3 Nf6 {[%cal Gc5c4]}
10. a4 (10. Nf3 c4 11. dxc4 bxc4 12. Ba4 Bd7 13. O-O Rc8 $11 {0-1 (39) Sutton,
A (2283)-Grayland,S (2367) ICCF email 2015}) 10... c4 11. axb5 Nb4 12. Ba4 cxd3
13. cxd3 Bd6 14. f4 Qa5 15. Bd2 Ng4 $15 {0-1 (43) Sutton,A (2297)-Ellis,L 
(2324) ICCF email 2015}) 4. Nxe4 Nd7 {Black gets a very solid caro style
structure here.} 5. d4 Ndf6 {[%cal Gd8d4]} 6. c3 Nxe4 7. Qxe4 Nf6 8. Qc2 Qd5 {
[%cal Gc8f5]}) (2. Bc4 {Giving us a free tempo} d5 3. Bb3 $5 {White gambits
the pawn for basically scholar's mate} dxe4 4. Qh5 e6 (4... g6) 5. Nc3 Nf6 6.
Qh4 Nbd7 {[%cal Gd7c5]} 7. f3 (7. Nxe4 Nxe4 8. Qxe4 Nc5 $15 {[%csl Rb3]}) 7...
Nc5 $5 (7... exf3 8. Nxf3 b5 {is recommended by my computer}) 8. fxe4 Nfxe4) (
2. b3 {Trying to establish a strong fianchettoed bishop and taking the game
down original paths} d5 3. Bb2 $5 {White's goal is some kind of aggressive
setup with opposite side castling but we have no complains as the fianchetto
