Summary: Our last section delt with many unusual options from White. Some I
think are not good at all (B3, Bc4, Blackmar-Diemer) but others require some
knowledge (Nf3+d3, Qe2/Qf3 & Ne2!?). In my experience 2. d3 is the most
popular of the bunch but allows us to take over the center. 2. Ne2!? is
probably the trickiest as the resulting positions are very confusing.
Elsewhere 2. Nf3 w/d3!? is a modern approach that may gain more popularity at
master level.} *

